}}</ref> and one of the most prominent early [[Diwan (poetry)|Divan]] masters in [[Turkic language|Turkic]] literary history,<ref name="nesimibritannica" /> who also composed poetry in [[Persian language|Persian]]<ref name="burrill" /><ref name="babinger">{{cite web
|url= http://www.brillonline.nl/subscriber/entry?entry=islam_SIM-5892
